Installation of jrat software is driven by ant and requires one optional
argument passed to the build script: 

install.prefix :: installation prefix / target directory

Example of installation command:

$ ant -Dinstall.prefix=/opt/baltrad install

In this case the software will be installed under /opt/baltrad/jrat

After the software is installed succesfully, you should add jrat/bin folder
to your $PATH e.g.
$ PATH=$PATH:/opt/baltrad/jrat/bin
$ export PATH

or run the application from the bin path.

When jrat is installed and ready to run you will receive help information on how
to use the software by:
$ jrat --help

